    "Numerical validation The system of herders and targets described in Equations (1) and ( 4) is simulated by using Forward Euler to integrate the ODEs and finite differences to integrate the PDE [27].",
    "The spatial domain is discretized uniformly with a step size ∆x.",
    "Two different time step sizes were used: a larger ∆t for the ODEs and a much smaller ∆t PDE for the PDE, following the guidelines in [27] for numerical stability.",
    "Table I summarizes the parameters used for simulations.",
    "The choice of parameters in Table I reflects realistic constraints in robotic shepherding applications, with herder velocities bounded by physical actuator limits and diffusion coefficient chosen to model moderate environmental noise.PPO was implemented following the algorithm proposed in [25]."
